---
import { Image } from "astro:assets";
import Layout from "../layouts/Layout.astro";
import img from "../../public/images/study_plan_reflection.png";
---

<Layout pageTitle="Study Reflection">
    <div class="page-container">
        <h1>Study Reflection</h1>

        <div class="reflection-container">
            <div class="image-wrapper">
                <Image
                    src={img}
                    alt="Study Reflection Portrait"
                    class="reflection-image"
                />
            </div>
            <div class="reflection-text">
                <p>
                    My study plan remained largely the same as the one I
                    originally came up with. My original intention was to begin
                    with AI-oriented courses and then explore GMT-related
                    topics, to get a broader view of directions I might want to
                    pursue, both during my thesis and my career after
                    graduation. Notably, I ended up learnign that I enjoy
                    project-focused courses significantly more, so I decided to
                    switch out Natural Language Processing with Serious Gaming,
                    which better aligned with my learning goals.
                </p>
                <p>
                    During this year, I believe I learned a lot about doing
                    research, both in theory and in practice. I carried out a
                    variety of user studies, using interviews, surveys, vignette
                    and observational studies, and gained experience with
                    analyzing both qualitative and quantitative data. I also
                    learned a lot about human factors in courses like Multimodal
                    Interaction and Cognitive Modeling, while also learning how
                    to code functional prototypes in courses like Serious
                    Gaming, Interaction Technology Innovation and Machine
                    Learning for Human Vision and Language.
                </p>
                <p>
                    For my remaining year, I decided to narrow my focus, and
                    prioritize courses that I anticipate will be most useful for
                    my thesis. To that effect, I dropped both Sound and Music
                    Technology and Social Computing from my plan. I added
                    Natural Language Generation as an additional course I would
                    be interested in taking, depending on how demanding my
                    thesis ends up being.
                </p>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>
</Layout>

<style>
    .reflection-container {
        display: flex;
        flex-direction: column;
        align-items: center;
        gap: 2rem;
        margin-top: 2rem;
        max-width: 800px;
        margin-left: auto;
        margin-right: auto;
    }

    .image-wrapper {
        width: 100%;
        max-width: 700px;
        border-radius: 12px;
        overflow: hidden;
        box-shadow: 0 4px 20px rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.1);
        transition: transform 0.3s ease;
    }

    .image-wrapper:hover {
        transform: translateY(-4px);
    }

    .reflection-image {
        width: 100%;
        height: auto;
        display: block;
        object-fit: cover;
    }

    .reflection-text {
        font-size: 1.1rem;
        line-height: 1.8;
        color: var(--color-text);
        text-align: justify;
    }

    .reflection-text p {
        margin-bottom: 1.5rem;
    }
</style>
